(firstQuint)Study of Autologous Bone Marrow Concentrate for the Treatment of Critical Limb Ischemia (CLI).

 Bone marrow aspirate is collected and processed by centrifugation to remove red blood cells.

 The buffy coat is concentrated by removing plasma.

 The resultant concentrate of cells is injected into ischemic tissues of the lower limb.

